\\\"sorry, not sorry\\\").\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The dad ad-libs\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"the letter\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1163}, {\"ngram\": \"daughter\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1203}, {\"ngram\": \"Syney's world\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We do not see the full contents of the letter, presumably because it is not very good and not at all inspiring because it is completely bereft of any human emotion, let alone his daughter's unique feelings about her hero.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the full contents\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1319}, {\"ngram\": \"the letter\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1333}, {\"ngram\": \"any human emotion\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"his daughter's unique feelings\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"her hero\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anyway, the ad appears to have done the unthinkable, and draw condemonation from across the internet.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1612, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ad\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1525}, {\"ngram\": \"condemonation\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1586}, {\"ngram\": \"the internet\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Various prominent commentators have decried the way the ad robs the child of being able to express her own creativity, by defaulting to the AI.\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1753, \"end\": 1755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999996125553, \"rank\": 3.876416298755672e-10, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Various prominent commentators\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1664}, {\"ngram\": \"the ad\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"the child\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1686}, {\"ngram\": \"her own creativity\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Washington Post's Alexandra Petri gloriouslywrote: \\\"I hate the Gemini 'Dear Sydney' ad more every passing moment,\\\" and proclaimed a desire to take a sledgehammer to the telly.\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1758, \"end\": 1777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0838894913393519e-24, \"text\": \"The Washington Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\"}, {\"begin\": 1780, \"end\": 1795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Petri\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexandra Petri\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Petri\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Petri\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Gemini 'Dear Sydney' ad\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1848}, {\"ngram\": \"a desire\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"a sledgehammer\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1923}, {\"ngram\": \"the telly\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She writes: \\\"What will these buffoons come up with next?\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these buffoons\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1976}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Gemini, propose for me\\\"?\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2021, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gemini\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Gemini, tell my parents I love them\\\"?\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2060, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gemini\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2029}, {\"ngram\": \"my parents\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lying on your death bed, \\\"Gemini, write a letter to my children saying all the things I wish I'd been able to tell them\\\"?\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2182, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your death bed\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"Gemini\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2093}, {\"ngram\": \"a letter\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"my children\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2124}, {\"ngram\": \"all the things\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What was my favorite thing about being alive?\\\"\\\"\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2231, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my favorite thing\", \"from\": 2193, \"to\": 2210}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alexandra also says, pointedly: \\\"To take away the ability to write for yourself is to take away the ability to think for yourself.\\\"\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2233, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_of_Denmark\", \"score\": 0.9999997652803634, \"rank\": 1.238444516179585e-07, \"text\": \"Alexandra\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_of_Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_of_Denmark\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ability\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2290}, {\"ngram\": \"the ability\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, NPR's Linda Holmeswrites: \\\"I promise you, if they are able, the words your kid can put together will be more meaningful than anything a prompt can spit out.\", \"from\": 2366, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2377, \"end\": 2380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5411117794727345e-14, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}, {\"begin\": 2383, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_McMahon\", \"score\": 0.9329878025938769, \"rank\": 0.07182394678441927, \"text\": \"Linda\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_McMahon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_McMahon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the words\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2446}, {\"ngram\": \"your kid\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2455}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2510}, {\"ngram\": \"a prompt\", \"from\": 2511, \"to\": 2519}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sit down with your kid and write the letter with them!\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2588, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your kid\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2556}, {\"ngram\": \"the letter\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just so grossed out by the entire thing.\\\"\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2635, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the entire thing\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2633}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore; Shelly Palmer, a media professor at Syracuse University,adds: \\\"The father in the video is not encouraging his daughter to learn to express herself.\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\"}, {\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999950632628, \"rank\": 2.568081082024011e-09, \"text\": \"Syracuse University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a media professor\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2682}, {\"ngram\": \"The father\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"the video\", \"from\": 2727, \"to\": 2736}, {\"ngram\": \"his daughter\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of guiding her to use her own words and communicate authentically, he is teaching her to rely on AI for this critical human skill.\\\"\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 2937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2903, \"end\": 2905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999996125553, \"rank\": 3.876416298755672e-10, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her own words\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2841}, {\"ngram\": \"this critical human skill\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even Gemini itself thinks the ad sucked, as the AI admitted to anAxios journalist.\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2987, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999996125553, \"rank\": 3.876416298755672e-10, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even Gemini\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2950}, {\"ngram\": \"the ad\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 2971}, {\"ngram\": \"anAxios journalist\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can see the answer, actually expressed quite well, below.\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3083, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the answer\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3044}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The condemnation is a stark reminder of how Silicon Valley continues to force feed generative AI tools like Gemini down the throats of a consumer base that has never once asked for this means of discouraging human creativity, which happens to be systematically undermining those who make their living that way, while ensuring there'll be no need for another generation to follow them.\", \"from\": 3085, \"to\": 3469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3179, \"end\": 3181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999996125553, \"rank\": 3.876416298755672e-10, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 3193, \"end\": 3199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9992979979709067, \"rank\": 0.0007024951821673669, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The condemnation\", \"from\": 3085, \"to\": 3101}, {\"ngram\": \"a stark reminder\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3121}, {\"ngram\": \"Silicon Valley\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3143}, {\"ngram\": \"the throats\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3216}, {\"ngram\": \"a consumer base\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3235}, {\"ngram\": \"this means\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3276}, {\"ngram\": \"human creativity\", \"from\": 3293, \"to\": 3309}, {\"ngram\": \"their living\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3385}, {\"ngram\": \"no need\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3430}, {\"ngram\": \"another generation\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please\\u2026 make it stop.\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3492, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chris Smith is a freelance technology journalist who has contributed news and reviews to Trusted 